ncture of anthropological explorations of the state, border studies, and research on transnational trade and infrastructure development, Borderland infrastructures provides new analytical tools to understand how state power is experienced, mediated, and enacted in Xinjiang and Yunnan. In the process, Rippa offers a rich and nuanced ethnography of life across China's peripheries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aBorderlandsxEconomic aspectszChina. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zChinazXinjiang Uygur Zizhiqu. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zChinazYunnan Sheng. 0aIntergovernmental fiscal relationszChina. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aInternational Relations. 4aPolitical Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Trade & Tariffs.2bisacsh  aAnthropology.  aBelt and Road Initiative.  aBorder studies.  aChina.  aInfrastructure.1 aHarris, Tina.1 aSchendel, Willem.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z9783